From b2751986dc636f3033a9e45d1199de742cbd5115 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 17:46:08 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] 8.3: rename source-side asset path strings for no-LFN DOS
 compatibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8 LFN-Option-B execution (task #28). NXEngine-evo's source has
hard-coded long-filename references to assets that violate DOS 8.3
naming. Under `lfn = false` DOSBox-X (and on real DOS without an LFN
TSR) these long names are inaccessible. This patch trues up the source
strings to 8.3-compliant equivalents; companion patches 0034 (data-file
renames) and 0035 (sprites.sif binary regeneration) close the loop on
disk and in the binary sprite manifest.

Renames in this patch (source strings only, mixed-case preserved to
match existing convention; DOS is case-insensitive but Linux dev hosts
aren't):

  src/sound/Organya.cpp
    "wavetable.dat" -> "wavetbl.dat"

  src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
    "music_dirs.json" -> "musicdir.jsn"
    "music.json"      -> "music.jsn"        (×2 push_back sites)
    error-log strings updated to match

  src/i18n/translate.cpp
    "system.json" -> "system.jsn"

  src/tsc.cpp
    "StageSelect.tsc" -> "StgSel.tsc"

  src/map.cpp
    "StageMeta/%s.json" -> "StgMeta/%s.jsn"
    (NB: also closes the directory-name 8.3 violation gap — `StageMeta`
     is 9 chars and would have been auto-truncated to STAGEM~1 under
     DOS short-name aliasing, which is fragile across CF cards.
     `StgMeta` is unambiguous + 8.3-clean.)

  src/endgame/credits.cpp
    "endpic/credit%02dm.bmp" -> "endpic/credt%02dm.bmp"
    (the `m` suffix variant is the primary; the non-`m` fallback at
     line 283 is left unchanged because `credit01.bmp` is already
     8.3-compliant — 8 char stem.)

  src/stagedata.cpp
    tileset_names[14]: "Almond" -> "Almnd"
    (drives both Stage/Almnd.pxa and Stage/PrtAlmnd.pbm path generation
     via map.cpp:66 sprintf and Tileset.cpp:40 sprintf respectively.)

Not renamed (intentionally):
  src/map.cpp:560 — the `+ "480fix.pbm"` branch generates names like
  bkFog480fix.pbm (11-char stem) but is gated on
  `Renderer::widescreen`, which is forced false on DOS by patch
  0005-renderer-lock-320x240-fullscreen.patch. Dead-code path; rename
  unnecessary. The 5 bk*480fix.pbm files are excluded from staging
  via a Makefile change in this same patch series.

Mod-compatibility implication: Cave Story mods authored against the
canonical Cave Story long names (Npc/NpcBallos.pbm, etc.) won't load.
Decision: 8.3-only for now per CLAUDE.md modder-friendly scope; revisit
at task #10 (mod stretch) with a possible ResourceManager fallback
layer that tries both 8.3 and long names.

Companion patch 0034 renames the corresponding data files in
vendor/nxengine-evo/data/ + the StageMeta directory.
Companion patch 0035 regenerates vendor/nxengine-evo/data/sprites.sif
to update the embedded sheet-path strings.

Why DOS needs this: only DOS without an LFN driver enforces 8.3 at the
filesystem layer. Desktop builds see no functional change — the names
are just shorter; getPath() resolves both old and new equivalently.
---
